A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Initial design and development efforts required to field LCS Class Ships with contractor furnished equipment is complete and tasking is removed from this section.

 This budget provides funds for the design, development, engineering, implementation, and testing of the combat system modifications for Lethality and Survivability
 (L&S) for both LCS variants (Independence and Freedom). The L&S upgrades include the development of a common Combat Management System (CMS) the Atalanta
 Weapon System (AtWS) and integration and testing of government furnished systems including the Gun Weapon System (GWS), Electronic Warfare (EW) system, and
 Decoy Launching System (DLS), and Navigation systems for the LCS Independence Class Variant ships. LCS CMS integration with Over The Horizon (OTH) targeting
 enable LCS to take advantage of full range capability of Naval Strike Missile (NSM). Follow on AtWS software (SW) development will incorporate corrections based on
 observations during shipboard testing and incremental capability increases to L&S ships.

