Remarks
This program is an integral part of the Army Integrated Air and Missile Defense (AIAMD) architecture.

D. Acquisition Strategy
In support of the Army's enduring Cruise Missile Defense requirement, the Army utilized an MTA RP approach to evaluate new capability and provide an initial capability.
In support of the IFPC Inc 2 solution, the Army pursued a competitive strategy that saw industry participating in a "Shoot Off" demonstration in FY 2021 using industry's
proposed launcher and missile solutions integrated with the Army's IBCS and Sentinel radar. The Army evaluated industry's proposals informed by models and
simulations, hardware-in-the-loop, and live fire data, to make a best value recommendation to proceed to a single vendor to deliver the IFPC Inc 2 prototype solution.
The Army awarded a Firm Fixed Price Other Transaction Authority (OTA) agreement to Dynetics, Inc. on 24 September 2021 to deliver the IFPC Inc 2 prototype
solution. In April 2025, the program transitioned to an MTA RF.


